<subSubSection id="588D01A54A7522B1602723FF51D66B90" pageId="0" pageNumber="129" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="7E39227EF067A03BBEACF47230BB9864" pageId="0" pageNumber="129">Diagnosis.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="405A164591793B95AB5E427BA02AB934" pageId="0" pageNumber="129">
<taxonomicName id="6537D538BBC0259DC60C95E39675C3F7" authorityName="Miq. first published in Fl. Ned. Ind. 1 (2): 630" authorityYear="1859" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Anacardiaceae" genus="Mangifera" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Mangifera sumatrana" order="Sapindales" pageId="0" pageNumber="129" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="sumatrana">
<emphasis id="C81619EE6579554D65B04C93C95DF39D" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="129">Mangifera sumatrana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has been considered as a synonym of 
<taxonomicName id="CE7CBF7AB0D36A0597D2AD0D88D71432" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Anacardiaceae" genus="Mangifera" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Mangifera laurina" order="Sapindales" pageId="0" pageNumber="129" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="laurina">
<emphasis id="A34C5438CF31145062EDB1C9B4CFF25F" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="129">Mangifera laurina</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Bl. The distinctive characteristics of the 
<taxonomicName id="AE8743A46FE1593665EBF1342E1B4040" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Anacardiaceae" genus="M." kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="M. sumatrana" order="Sapindales" pageId="0" pageNumber="129" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="sumatrana">
<emphasis id="78B98E4BA39F95BFCF8F70187A738AFC" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="129">M. sumatrana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
are panicles pyramidal and not dense, large and flat fruit, prominent fruit beak type, a quantity of fibre in pulp and high stone. 
<taxonomicName id="FFBE8EE10DF1FD1B486C6B5220DB3F28" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Anacardiaceae" genus="M." kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="M. laurina" order="Sapindales" pageId="0" pageNumber="129" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="laurina">
<emphasis id="2A7977C14E2558FFED643E780F96B1C7" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="129">M. laurina</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
panicles are conical and dense, with small and thick fruit, round in shape and fruit break type is perceptible (Figs 
<figureCitation id="3C4A26813DC7676E49F989DB814D238F" captionStart="Figure 1" captionStartId="F1" captionText="Figure 1. Mangifera sumatrana A habit B adaxial and abaxial surface of leaf C pyramidal panicles D flowers E flowers after anthesis; F ovary with swollen disc G roundish fruit H flattened fruit I pulp." figureDoi="10.3897/phytokeys.199.80727.figure1" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/693718" pageId="0" pageNumber="129">1</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="AB3C3E3E22E4A47B1B2D98B43BDC8158" captionStart="Figure 2" captionStartId="F2" captionText="Figure 2. Mangifera laurina A conical panicles B flowers C roundish thick fruit." figureDoi="10.3897/phytokeys.199.80727.figure2" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/693719" pageId="0" pageNumber="129">2</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<caption id="5D25A1CDF0EE6702F395E7B5E8F6EA96" doi="10.3897/phytokeys.199.80727.figure1" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/693718" pageId="0" pageNumber="129" start="Figure 1" startId="F1">
